The Cabinet has echoed a call by President Jacob Zuma for restraint in communities where tensions are high among locals and foreigners. PARLIAMENT - Cabinet has condemned the recent violence in Tshwane saying it is unacceptable.It has echoed a call by President Jacob Zuma for restraint in communities where tensions are high among locals and foreigners.At a post-Cabinet briefing at Parliament on Thursday morning, Minister in the Presidency Jeff Radebe said the police are prepared to act speedily against incidents of violence and looting. Crime is our common enemy and by working together we can address the issues that concern our communities. There s no room for acts of violence and intimidation. No grievance can ever justify members of communities taking the law into their own hands. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)